lass=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rmv1665702953363.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rmv1665702953363.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rmv1665702953363.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rmv1665702953363\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Database Access on ODBC\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__section_w3508ab1b5b1_w3509ab1b5_w3510ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__section_w3511ab1b5b3_w3512ab1b5_w3513ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d250629e59\">\n                        \n Logon Path Specification\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__p_d54761e1_d54762e1_d54763e1\">The logon path for the OD<var class=\"keyword varname\">x</var> Connector is specified with the following assignment:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$ODBC OD<var class=\"keyword varname\">x</var>:<var class=\"keyword varname\">DataSourceName</var>:|{<var class=\"keyword varname\">UserName</var>}|{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>}\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__p_d54764e1_d54765e1_d54766e1\">The DBMS logon form appears when Uniface accesses the DBMS for the first time.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__p_d54767e1_d54768e1_d54769e1\">The following information needs to be provided:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__li_d25259e1_d25260e1_d25261e1\">Database—<var class=\"keyword varname\">DataSourceName</var>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__li_d25262e1_d25263e1_d25264e1\">Identifier—<var class=\"keyword varname\">UserName</var>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__li_d25265e1_d25266e1_d25267e1\">Password—<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__note_w3517ab1b5b3c13_w3518ab1b5b3_w3519ab1b5_w3520ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> An ODBC database cannot be used for the Uniface Repository.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__section_w3514ab1b5b5_w3515ab1b5_w3516ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d250629e117\">\n                        \n Open/Close Support\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rmv1665702953363__p_d54773e1_d54774e1_d54775e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">close</span> instructions are supported. The <code class=\"ph codeph\">open</code> instruction opens the relevant path and attempts to log on to the database. The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">close</span> instruction closes all tables and logs off from the DBMS, shutting down that path.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lnl1665702774754.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Access</a><p>Uniface automatically opens the DBMS when a read or write ProcScript statement is issued. The path and logon details for the specific database (or databases) can be provided in an assignment file, a command line instruction, or in the open ProcScript instruction.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sbg1665702735473.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Paths and Path Assignments</a><p>A path is a named route to a resource required by the application, such as a database connector and database, a remote server, or a file location.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531692\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531692\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Database Access on ODBC Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Database Access on ODBC Logon Path Specification The logon path for the OD x Connector is specified with the following assignment: $ODBC OD x : DataSourceName :|{ UserName }|{ Password } Copy The DBMS logon form appears when Uniface accesses the DBMS for the first time. The following information needs to be provided: Database— DataSourceName Identifier— UserName Password— Password Note: An ODBC database cannot be used for the Uniface Repository. Open/Close Support The open and close instructions are supported. The open instruction opens the relevant path and attempts to log on to the database. The close instruction closes all tables and logs off from the DBMS, shutting down that path. Related Links Database Access Uniface automatically opens the DBMS when a read or write ProcScript statement is issued. The path and logon details for the specific database (or databases) can be provided in an assignment file, a command line instruction, or in the open ProcScript instruction. Paths and Path Assignments A path is a named route to a resource required by the application, such as a database connector and database, a remote server, or a file location. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}